Appendix B: Technical Specifications & Protocols

B.1 AWR Intelligence Platform: Core Data Inputs & Specifications

Data Stream Source/Provider Frequency Key Parameters Measured Integration Purpose
Satellite Data EUMETSAT (MSG), Copernicus (Sentinel) 5-15 min (real-time) Cloud top temp, liquid water path, particle size, wind vectors Seedability Index (SI) calculation, target identification
National Radar Network Direction de la Météorologie Nationale (DMN) 5 min Reflectivity, Doppler velocity, precipitation rate Real-time storm tracking, post-op verification
Automatic Weather Stations (AWS) Dense network in target basins 1 min Temp, RH, pressure, wind, rain gauge Microclimate validation, ground-truthing
UAV Atmospheric Profilers Program-owned drones Per mission Vertical profiles of temp, RH, aerosol concentration Pre- and post-seeding atmospheric state analysis
Numerical Model Output Moroccan Atmospheric Digital Twin (MADT) 6-hour forecast cycles Simulated cloud fields, stability indices 72-hr SI probabilistic forecasting

B.2 Seeding Fleet & Material Specifications

· Manned Aircraft (King Air C90GT):
  · Payload: Wing-mounted pyrotechnic flare dispensers, hygroscopic flare dispensers, cloud particle imagers (CPI), GPS dropsonde launcher.
  · Modification: Installation of satellite telemetry for live data feed to the AWR Platform.
· Unmanned Aerial System (UAS - Fixed Wing):
  · Specification: Minimum 6-hour endurance, 100km range, capable of operating at -20°C.
  · Payload: Lightweight aerosol dispersers, basic meteorological sensors.
  · Role: Pre-seeding atmospheric sampling, targeted seeding in valleys, post-op verification.
· Seeding Materials Protocol:
  · Primary (Cold Clouds < -5°C): Silver Iodide (AgI) pyrotechnic flares. Environmental Audit: Annual soil and water sampling in target areas to monitor Ag+ ion accumulation against a pre-defined baseline (0.1 ppb trigger for review).
  · Secondary (Warm Clouds): Potassium Chloride (KCl) hygroscopic flares.
  · Research & Development Stream: Dedicated 5% of operational budget to test and validate third-generation, biodegradable nuclei (e.g., tailored proteins, nanocellulose).

---

Appendix C: Economic Model & Funding Framework

C.1 Social License-Adjusted Return (SLAR) Calculation

The SLAR is the primary metric determining the program's annual budget allocation within the national water portfolio.

Formula:
SLAR = (Ve + Vi + Va) * C_p

· Ve (Economic Value): (Additional m³ of water generated) × (Marginal cost of alternative water source, e.g., desalination).
· Vi (Infrastructure Value): Estimated reduction in wear/depletion of dams and aquifers.
· Va (Avoided Loss Value): Estimated value of agricultural losses prevented or drought emergency costs avoided.
· C_p (Public Confidence Coefficient): A dimensionless number from 0.0 to 1.5, derived from the ASC's annual public perception survey. 1.0 = Baseline public trust.

Example: If a season generates €15M in total value (Ve+Vi+Va) but the C_p is 0.7 due to public mistrust, the SLAR = €10.5M. This discounted value is used in portfolio analysis.

C.2 Proposed Multi-Source Funding Structure (Year 3-5)

Funding Source Mechanism Allocated Purpose % of Total Budget
National Water Fund Direct annual appropriation Core NAWRA operations, salaries, maintenance 50%
Beneficiary Levy Surcharge on increased water deliveries to high-value agriculture/industry in target zones Technology upgrades, R&D 20%
Green Climate/Sovereign Bonds International climate adaptation funds; issuance of "Water Security Bonds" Capital expenditure (drones, radar upgrades) 20%
Public-Private Partnership Long-term service contract with a private operator for UAS fleet management UAS operations and innovation 10%

---

Appendix D: Operational Protocols & Templates

D.1 Mission Authorization Checklist (To be completed by NAWRA & ASC)

· Forecast Validation: SI for target zone > 0.65 (High Confidence) for the 6-hour operation window.
· Hydrological Coordination: Confirmation received from relevant River Basin Agency that target reservoir has capacity or aquifer recharge site is prepared.
· Environmental Clearance: Wind models confirm plume remains >10km from designated protected ecological zones.
· Diplomatic Clearance (if within 150km of border): Pre-notification log shared with IHD shows confirmation receipt from Spanish counterpart.
· Public Notification: Mission advisory (time, general area, purpose) posted to Public Dashboard 24 hours prior.
· ASC "No-Objection": ASC liaison officer has acknowledged the mission packet.

D.2 Post-Operation Impact Assessment Template

Mission ID: [BG-YYYY-BASIN-XXX]
Date: [DD/MM/YYYY]
Target Basin: [e.g., Upper Oum er Rbia]

1. Operational Summary:
   · Seeding Material & Amount Dispersed: [e.g., 12 x AgI flares]
   · Aircraft Flight Path & Altitude: [Link to Dashboard Track]
   · Actual vs. Forecasted Atmospheric Conditions: [Brief analysis]
2. Hydrological Impact (Preliminary - 30 Days Post-Op):
   · Rain Gauge Network Analysis: [Table showing precipitation in target vs. control areas]
   · Estimated Additional Water Generated: [X] m³
   · Reservoir Inflow Observation: [Data from dam authority]
3. Environmental Monitoring Note:
   · No anomalies reported from automatic air/water quality sensors.
   · Next scheduled soil sampling: [Date].
4. ASC Remarks & Status: [For ASC use: "Cleared," "Pending Review," or "Audit Required."]

